node.text: Unwrapped with Martin House! A new video series where we drink a lot of coffee and rip off the shrink wraps really fast to see what’s underneath. What will it be this time!? #stellar

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Martin House Brewing Co. on August 23, 2021 tagging @bestmaidpickles.

node.text: 🍇This week we release Grape Punch Pickle Beer 6.5%. This unique flavor is inspired by the southern delicacy “koolickles” or Koolaid pickles, to the layperson. Koolickles happen when you combine a packet of Koolaid and some sugar in your pickle jar and let them rest for a few days. It’s strangely delicious and addictive (recipe coming soon!) The sour pickle beer combined with the grape punch flavor creates the perfect summertime treat! Thanks to Best Maid as always! Grape Punch Pickle Beer is limited and will be distributed this week. 4packs are also available to-go starting today at noon in the taproom. Can’t wait for yall to try it! Cheers! #pickles #picklebeer #bestmaid #martinhouse #grapepunch #koolaid #koolickles #fortworth #texas #madeintexasbytexans

node.text: Bring your tents! Bring the fam! Bring the doggos. It’s time for another backyard party at martin house. Doors open at 12pm. We have some badass vendors and food trucks out here today. Can’t wait to see yall. Cheers! #martinhouse #fortworth #fortworthtx #seefortworth #eatfortworth #drinkfortworth #craftfortworth

node.text: Here we go! Tomorrow is the great pickle party. This is a lot of info, but if you are planning on coming out, you should def read this. NEW - beer to-go only purchases (those not hanging around and drinking tomorrow) should enter in the back by the stairs. But yeah. It’ll be another great backyard hang. Super chill. Excited to see all your faces again. Cheers! #thegreatpickleparty (also all of this info is in the FB event page if that’s more friendly for viewing on your particular phone).

node.text: 🥒 This is looking nice! These are four of the 40+ beers on tap this Saturday for the great pickle party. It aint all pickle beers, but there will be a lot of them. Food trucks, craft vendors, live tunes, and all the brewskis. Makes for a pretty solid backyard martin house rager. Tickets available at the door from noon to 5pm for $20 (covers the pint glass and four pours). There will be some special cans at beer to go also. See yall Saturday!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Martin House Brewing Co. on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, drink, food and indoor.

node.text: 🥧 Who wants pie? This week’s release is Key Lime Pie 6.2% - Lime Sour Ale Brewed with Graham Crackers and Lactose. This is our second year to release KLP. We know it’s a favorite of many, but for the newbies, you could easily compare it to our Lemon Icebox Pie. So take the citrus, creaminess, and graham cracker flavor and just replace lemon with lime. We love it! 6packs of Key Lime Pie continue distribution to our normal retailers all week long. We’ll have 6packs for sell in the taproom for $12 starting today at noon. Oh and we’re tapping up the first keg this Thursday at 4pm. Hope you dig it! Cheers! #keylimepie #keylime #lime #sourbeer #grahamcrackers #pie

node.text: MINI RAMP JAM! Saturday, August 14th, 12-5pm: @magnolia.skate.shop ramp out back, @beyondgrasp live graffiti, @djramobeats on the ones and twos, @fireflygrillinggo cooking up tacos, THPS2 playstation 2 freestyle on inside tv, 2 new limited edition MHBC tees debut…it’s going to be the best day ever. Cheers! #fortworth #skatefortworth #eatfortworth #drinkfortworth #seefortworth #hearfortworth #filmfortworth #fortworthtx #dfw #ilovefortworth #skate #graffiti #dj #tacos #tonyhawk #martinhouse #rage
